+# PHP Tip Calculator
+
+A single-page PHP web app that calculates the tip amount, bill total, and per-person amount owed.
+
+## Requirements
+
+- PHP 8.1 or newer
+- Composer is optional; there are no third-party dependencies
+
+## Run locally on port 5003
+
+Set a local secret with at least 32 characters, then start PHP's built-in server:
+
+```powershell
+$env:APP_SECRET = "replace-with-at-least-32-random-characters"
+php -S 127.0.0.1:5003 index.php
+```
+
+Or with Composer:
+
+```powershell
+$env:APP_SECRET = "replace-with-at-least-32-random-characters"
+composer run start
+```
+
+Open http://127.0.0.1:5003 in your browser.
+
+## Security notes
+
+- Input is allow-list validated server-side before calculation.
+- All dynamic output is HTML-escaped before rendering.
+- POST submissions include CSRF protection using HMAC-signed, time-limited tokens derived from `APP_SECRET`.
+- Session cookies are configured with `HttpOnly`, `Secure`, and `SameSite=Strict`.
+- Security headers include CSP, `X-Frame-Options`, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `Referrer-Policy`, and `Permissions-Policy`. HSTS is sent when served over HTTPS.
+- Runtime errors are logged server-side and generic errors are returned to clients.
+- Secrets are read from environment variables and are not hardcoded.
+- This app has no database, accounts, passwords, or user-owned resources. Therefore SQL injection, password hashing, and IDOR access-control paths do not exist in the runtime. If those features are added later, use PDO prepared statements for all queries, `password_hash()` with bcrypt or Argon2 for passwords, and ownership checks on every resource action.
